	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you wear the uniform, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> You carry more than anyone back home can see — the danger, the distance, the weight of the mission, the long nights far from family. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone, anywhere in the world — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for soldiers," "verses for courage," "protection," or "verses for deployment" — the answer starts in one place: you are never deployed beyond His reach. He goes with you wherever you go, and He will never leave you nor forsake you.`}
	keyTakeaway={`The answer to a service member's fear and distance isn't just discipline and duty — it's a Father who goes with you wherever you are deployed, who never leaves His post, and who promises He will not leave you nor forsake you.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight service members carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel the strain of distance, danger, and being expected to be tough no matter what, you are not weak and you are not alone. A whole force is carrying the same weight — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `230,000+`, label: `U.S. service members deploy overseas in a typical year, many separated from family for months at a time (DoD, 2023)` },
		{ value: `1 in 3`, label: `active-duty members report their work-life or deployment tempo as a top source of stress (Blue Star Families Survey, 2023)` },
		{ value: `37%`, label: `of active-duty family respondents cite time away from family as a top stressor of military life (Blue Star Families Survey, 2023)` },
		{ value: `523`, label: `active-duty service members died by suicide in 2023 — every loss a life the force is working to protect (DoD Annual Suicide Report, 2023)` },
		{ value: `~9%`, label: `of active-duty members screen positive for probable generalized anxiety in a given year (DoD health studies)` },
		{ value: `31%`, label: `of service members report getting 5 hours of sleep or less on a typical night (DoD health surveys)` },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real service member — maybe you. The deployment that puts an ocean between you and the people you love. The danger you can't always name in a phone call home. The moral weight of a mission that asks more of you than anyone outside the uniform understands. The pressure to be tough when you're exhausted, anxious, or just lonely.</p><p>None of this means something is wrong with you. It means you're human, doing one of the hardest jobs there is, in places far from home. There is a Father who sees the real you under the body armor — who doesn't need you to be tough to be loved — and He has something to say about who you are and where He is standing.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: `Department of Defense — CY2023 Annual Report on Suicide in the Military`, url: `https://www.dspo.mil/Portals/113/2024/documents/annual_report/ARSM_CY23_final_508c.pdf` },
		{ label: `Pew Research — The American Veteran Experience`, url: `https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2019/09/10/the-american-veteran-experience-and-the-post-9-11-generation/` },
		{ label: `Blue Star Families — Military Family Lifestyle Survey`, url: `https://bluestarfam.org/research/mfls-results/` },
	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for service members`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what the training doesn't tell you: the answer to the fear and the distance isn't only discipline, duty, and grit. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who goes with you wherever you are sent, and who never stands down from watching over you.</p><p>You were not made to carry the weight of the mission alone. The God who made you doesn't measure you by how tough you can stay or how much you can endure in silence. He calls you His own, and He makes you a promise no commander could keep: <em>I will never leave you nor forsake you.</em> Not in the field. Not on the worst night. Not one mile from home or ten thousand.</p><p>So before you are a soldier, a sailor, an airman, a Marine, a Guardian — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady presence beside you in the dark, the One who says: I see you, I'm with you, and I never left your side.</p>`}
