	verses={[
		{ ref: `Joshua 1:9`, slug: `joshua`, ch: 1, text: `Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid, and do not be discouraged, for I, your Father, am with you wherever you go.`, note: `Wherever the orders send you, your Father has already gone with you — you are never deployed alone.` },
		{ ref: `Deuteronomy 31:6`, slug: `deuteronomy`, ch: 31, text: `Be strong and courageous. Do not fear or dread them, for your Father goes with you; He will never leave you nor forsake you.`, note: `No commander can promise this — your Father can: He will never leave His post beside you.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 41:10`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 41, text: `Fear not, for I am with you; do not be dismayed, for I am your Father. I will strengthen you and help you; I will uphold you with My righteous right hand.`, note: `When the fear rises, your Father is holding you up — you don't have to be strong on your own.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 91:1-2`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 91, text: `Whoever dwells in the shelter of the Most High will rest in the shadow of the Almighty. I will say of my Father, He is my refuge and my fortress, my God, in whom I trust.`, note: `The Father is the fortress that travels with you — cover for the soul no enemy can breach.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 23:4`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `Even though I walk through the darkest valley, I will fear no evil, for You are with me; Your rod and Your staff, they comfort me.`, note: `Even in the valley of the shadow, you do not walk it alone — your Father walks it with you.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 121:7-8`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 121, text: `Your Father will keep you from all harm — He will watch over your life; He will watch over your coming and going, both now and forevermore.`, note: `Your coming and your going, your deployment and your homecoming — He is watching over all of it.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:6-7`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything, by prayer, bring your requests to your Father — and His peace, beyond all understanding, will guard your heart and mind.`, note: `Hand the worry you can't say out loud to your Father, and let His peace stand watch over your heart.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 43:2`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 43, text: `When you pass through the waters, I will be with you; and through the rivers, they will not overwhelm you. When you walk through fire, you will not be burned, for I am your Father.`, note: `Through the waters and through the fire, He does not send you ahead — He goes through it with you.` },
		{ ref: `2 Timothy 1:7`, slug: `2-timothy`, ch: 1, text: `For your Father did not give you a spirit of fear, but a spirit of power, of love, and of a sound mind.`, note: `The fear is not from Him — your Father has given you power, love, and a steady mind to stand on.` },
	]}
	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers you`}
	offersIntroHtml={`The mission asks you to keep proving you can carry it. Here's what your Father gives you instead — for free, because you are already His.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `A Father who deploys with you`, bodyHtml: `You are never sent alone: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/joshua/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">your Father is with you wherever you go</a> — every post, every patrol, every night far from home. No distance puts you beyond His reach.` },
		{ heading: `A promise no one can revoke`, bodyHtml: `Commands change, units rotate, but your Father makes one promise that holds: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/deuteronomy/31" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">He will never leave you nor forsake you</a> — not in the field, not on the worst day.` },
		{ heading: `Protection and refuge`, bodyHtml: `When the danger is real, your Father is a fortress that travels with you: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/91" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">He is your refuge and your shield</a>, watching over your coming and your going.` },
		{ heading: `Peace for the fear and the weight`, bodyHtml: `You don't have to carry it tough and alone: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/philippians/4" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">hand your worries to your Father</a>, and His peace — the kind that doesn't even make sense — guards your heart and mind.` },
	]}
	whyHeading={`Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for service members`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet God as a Father who deploys with you`, bodyHtml: `Most Bibles can read like another chain of command. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1</a> on. So instead of one more voice telling you to be tough, you meet the One who goes with you wherever you are sent and never stands down from your side.` },
		{ heading: `It's free, on your phone, anywhere in the world`, bodyHtml: `No account, no purchase, no app. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Read it free online</a> with audio on every chapter — read it on your phone in the barracks, listen on a long flight, or open it on the night watch. Spotty connection? Load a chapter when you have signal and the Father's voice goes with you off-grid.` },
		{ heading: `It speaks to fear, distance, and danger`, bodyHtml: `Afraid? Far from home? Carrying more than you can say? Start with our <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a> for courage, protection, and peace, or learn to talk to Him with our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> — the Word meets you right where you stand.` },
	]}
	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`Wherever you are deployed, you are not beyond His reach. The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father who goes with you, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Andrew Murray, George MacDonald, and Charles Spurgeon (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel different the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's presence isn't a rush of adrenaline — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one watch at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that the distance and the danger can't uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I know where they've sent you. I see the post you're standing, the miles between you and the ones you love, the fear you don't let anyone hear. And I want you to know it over all of it: I go with you. There is no deployment, no valley, no dark that puts you beyond My reach — I am with you wherever you go.</p><p>You don't have to be strong enough to earn My presence, and you'll never march so far that I lose sight of you. I never leave My post. When the fear comes, lean into Me — I'll strengthen you, steady your mind, and watch over your coming and your going. You are never out of My sight, and I will never leave you nor forsake you."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for service members`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these service members — every soldier, sailor, airman, Marine, and Guardian standing watch far from home. Go with them wherever they are deployed. Be their refuge and their fortress, their shield in danger and their steady presence in the long, lonely nights. Let them know they are never beyond Your reach.</p><p>Father, guard their hearts and minds with the peace that passes understanding. Lift the fear they carry in silence, ease the weight of the mission, and give them a sound mind and rest for their bodies. Strengthen them with Your right hand, and let them feel You walking beside them through every valley and every fire.</p><p>We pray too for the families waiting at home — the spouses, the children, the parents counting the days. Hold them close, comfort the empty seat at the table, and carry them through the distance. Bring every one of these service members home in Your time, and let them know You, their Father, as the One who never left their side.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
