	keepReadingHtml={`Start with the <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">whole Bible free online with audio</a>, learn <a href="/the-fathers-heart-bible/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">why the Father's Heart Bible™ exists</a>, or get oriented with our <a href="/guides/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Bible reading guides</a> — including <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how to pray</a> and <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a>. Or meet the Father in another season of life across the <a href="/bible-for/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">A Father For series</a>.`}
	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for soldiers and service members?`, answer: `Joshua 1:9 (be strong and courageous, I am with you wherever you go), Deuteronomy 31:6 (He will never leave you nor forsake you), Isaiah 41:10 (fear not, I will uphold you), Psalm 91 (my refuge and my fortress), Psalm 23:4 (though I walk through the darkest valley), Psalm 121 (He will watch over your coming and going), Isaiah 43:2 (through the waters and the fire I am with you), and 2 Timothy 1:7 (a spirit of power, not fear) all speak straight to what service members carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about courage in danger and combat?`, answer: `Scripture meets fear head-on. Joshua 1:9 commands, "Be strong and courageous; do not be afraid, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go," and 2 Timothy 1:7 says God gave you a spirit of power, love, and a sound mind — not fear. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father who goes with you into the danger, not a distant figure watching from far off. Read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What Bible verses help with being deployed far from family?`, answer: `The distance never puts you outside God's reach. Psalm 139 says there is nowhere you can go from His presence, Deuteronomy 31:6 promises He will never leave you nor forsake you, and Psalm 121 says He watches over your coming and your going. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet God as a Father who deploys with you and holds the family waiting at home, too. Read and listen free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does God care about my fear, anxiety, and the weight of the mission?`, answer: `Yes — deeply, and He invites you to bring it to Him. Philippians 4:6-7 says don't be anxious about anything, but bring your requests to God, and His peace will guard your heart and mind. Psalm 23 walks with you through the darkest valley. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet God as a Father you can actually hand the weight to — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio I can use while deployed?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone in the barracks, on a long flight, or on watch. Load a chapter when you have signal and you can read or listen to it wherever the mission takes you.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for the military?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice telling you to be tough, you meet the One who goes with you wherever you are sent. For a service member far from home, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child whose Father never leaves His post, not a soldier expected to carry it all alone.` },
		{ question: `How can I start reading the Bible while serving?`, answer: `Start small and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, pick a Psalm or a short book, and listen to the audio while you read — on watch, before a mission, or when you can't sleep. Try a verse a day; Psalm 91, Psalm 23, or Joshua 1 are strong places to begin. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words for whatever you're facing right now.` },
	]}
